error_message:
Cannot convert non-constant Pyomo expression (product_start['6122',HELGAS GFREE WHOLEM 500G,2025-10-28] + product_start['6122',HELGAS GFREE MIXED GRAIN 500G,2025-10-28] + product_start['6122',WONDER GFREE WHOLEM 500G,2025-10-28] + product_start['6122',WONDER GFREE WHITE 470G,2025-10-28] + product_start['6122',HELGAS GFREE TRAD WHITE 470G,2025-10-28] - 1  <  0) to bool.
This error is usually caused by using a Var, unit, or mutable Param in a
Boolean context such as an "if" statement, or when checking container
membership or equality. For example,
    >>> m.x = Var()
    >>> if m.x >= 1:
    ...     pass
and
    >>> m.y = Var()
    >>> if m.y in [m.x, m.y]:
    ...     pass
would both cause this exception.
